<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-20983] Paxos repair blocks response thread</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20983</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-20469&quot; title=&quot;Paxos repair interrupts running transactions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-20469&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-20469&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; prevented paxos repairs from preempting in progress paxos transactions by holding repairs until after they would have timed out. However, it added a sleep that&#8217;s often called in the request response stage, and with the PaxosCleanupLocalCoordinator lock held. This patch adjusts this by putting a delayed repair into a delayed queue, and scheduling a wakeup task for after the timeout expires.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
